==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delusive
<hw>De*lu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Delude</er>.]</ety> <def>Apt or fitted to delude; tending to mislead
the mind; deceptive; beguiling; delusory; <as>as, <ex>delusive</ex>
arts; a <ex>delusive</ex> dream.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Delusive</qex> and unsubstantial ideas.</q>
<rj><qau>Whewell.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>De*lu"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>De*lu"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delusory</ent>⟦br⟧
